description: dead +‎ -en. Compare Dutch doden (“to kill”), West Frisian deadzje (“to kill”).

verbs.description: deaden (third-person singular simple present deadens, present participle deadening, simple past and past participle deadened)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To render less lively; to diminish; to muffle.
(intransitive) To become less lively; to diminish (by itself).

examples: to deaden a wall or a floor
